          <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
            <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">How do I choose between a disc stack and decanter centrifuge?</summary>
            <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">The primary decision factors are: (1) <strong>Solids content</strong> — disc stack centrifuges handle &lt;2% solids; decanters handle up to 40%; (2) <strong>Particle size</strong> — disc stacks separate particles down to 0.5 microns; decanters handle &gt;100 microns; (3) <strong>Separation type</strong> — disc stacks excel at liquid-liquid separation (oil/water); decanters excel at solid-liquid separation (sludge dewatering).</p>
          </details>
